<paragraph id="8B8636F80436FFF1FF7FFB32FEF575FB" blockId="4.[151,629,1194,1257]" box="[151,318,1231,1257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FF7FFB32FEDD75FB" box="[151,278,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Figs 17, 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FECAFB32FEF575FB" box="[290,318,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-196@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., head in frontal view; 31 D. pilosa, female holotype; 32 D. costulata, female paratype; 33 D. carinifer, male paratype; 34 D. pedunculata, male paratype; 35 D. costulata, male paratype; 36 D. pilosa, male paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592906/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">33</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32365730436FFF1FF7FFAEBFBA674F7" pageId="4" pageNumber="325" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8636F80436FFF1FF7FFAEBFBA674F7" blockId="4.[151,1437,1302,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0436FFF1FF7FFAEBFEC17422" bold="true" box="[151,266,1302,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Head, including antennal flagellum, and mesosoma dark brown to black (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FB9AFAEAFB037423" box="[1138,1224,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
), legs with coxae, trochanters and femora dark brown, tibiae and tarsi yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FC4FFAC6FC317447" box="[935,1018,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), fore wing infumate with part below stigmal vein dark brown (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FE5CFAA2FDF8746B" box="[436,563,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Figs 17, 18</figureCitation>
), Gt 
<subScript id="17BD34BD0436FFF1FD8CFA8CFDA7746D" attach="left" box="[612,620,1393,1407]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">1</subScript>
yellowish-brown, Gt 
<subScript id="17BD34BD0436FFF1FCB1FA8CFCB9746D" attach="left" box="[857,882,1393,1407]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">2–7</subScript>
dark brown (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FBEBFAA2FB9D746B" box="[1027,1110,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); antenna with F2–4 (excluding apical stalk) about as long as wide with a short stalk in anterior part (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FC51FA7EFBC0748F" box="[953,1035,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); pronotal collar with a carina along anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FEB9FA5AFE6874D3" box="[337,419,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); midlobe of mesoscutum with three pairs of long and strong setae (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FB66FA5AFB2B74D3" box="[1166,1248,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); mesoscutellum with sublateral grooves joining in posterior part (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FD54FA36FCC474F7" box="[700,783,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); propodeum smooth (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0436FFF1FBE5FA36FBAB74F7" box="[1037,1120,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32365730436FFF0FF2FFA13FE697077" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="326" pageId="4" pageNumber="325" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8636F80436FFF1FF2FFA13FE7B77AF" blockId="4.[151,1437,1302,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0436FFF1FF2FFA13FDD0771A" bold="true" box="[199,539,1518,1544]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">
Description (male 
<typeStatus id="5482885A0436FFF1FE4CFA13FDC5771A" box="[420,526,1518,1544]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CC19B1D0436FFF1FD92FA13FD07771B" box="[634,716,1518,1545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="325" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5mm</quantity>
. Frons and vertex with weak reticulation. Pronotal collar with a carina along anterior margin. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum with weak reticulation; midlobe of mesoscutum with three pairs of long and strong setae; mesoscutellum with sublateral grooves joining in posterior part. Dorsellum and propodeum smooth; propodeal callus with six setae. Fore wing with six setae on dorsal surface of submarginal vein; with 12 admarginal setae; costal cell with a row of seven setae on ventral surface, apico-dorsal margin with three setae. Gaster short ovate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8636F80436FFF1FF2FF93AFBF4763B" blockId="4.[151,1437,1302,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">
Colour. Head dark brown to black. Antennae dark brown. Mesosoma dark brown to black. Legs with coxae, trochanters and femora dark brown, tibiae and tarsi yellowish-brown. Fore wing infumate with part below stigmal vein dark brown. Petiole black. Gaster with Gt 
<subScript id="17BD34BD0436FFF1FD49F8DCFD62763D" attach="left" box="[673,681,1825,1839]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">1</subScript>
yellowish-brown, Gt 
<subScript id="17BD34BD0436FFF1FC70F8DCFC7A763D" attach="left" box="[920,945,1825,1839]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">2–7</subScript>
dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8636F80436FFF0FF2FF8CEFDB771EB" blockId="4.[151,1437,1302,2013]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,150,1041]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="326" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">
Relative measurements. 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0436FFF1FE32F8CEFDD1765F" bold="true" box="[474,538,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Head</emphasis>
: length in dorsal view 15; length in frontal view 26; width 35; POL 8.5; OOL 4; mouth width 12; malar space 8; eye height 16.5; scape length 14; scape width 3; pedicel+flagellum length 45; F1 length 8; F2 length 7; F3 length 7; F4 length 7; antennal clava length 11; F1 width 4; F2 width 5; F3 width 5.5; F4 width 6; antennal clava width 5.5. 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0436FFF1FDCBF862FD6A76AB" bold="true" box="[547,673,1951,1977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="325">Mesosoma</emphasis>
: length 50; width 30; midlobe of mesoscutum length 19; mesoscutellum length 20; mesoscutellum width 14.5; dorsellum length 2; propodeum length 10; mid tarsus length 21; mid tarsus T4 length 4; hind tarsus length 21; hind tarsus T4 length 4.5; fore wing length 70; fore wing width 45; costal cell length 26; costal cell width 2; marginal vein length 29; postmarginal vein length 10; stigmal vein length 10. 
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FF7FFF23FF2371EA" bold="true" box="[151,232,222,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">Gaster</emphasis>
: length 47; width 27; Gt 
<subScript id="17BD34BD0437FFF0FE14FF0CFDCF71ED" attach="left" box="[508,516,241,255]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">1</subScript>
length 24.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8636F80437FFF0FF2FFEFEFD7B7053" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">
Variation in 
<typeStatus id="5482885A0437FFF0FEBCFEFEFE08700F" box="[340,451,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">paratypes</typeStatus>
. Length 
<quantity id="4CC19B1D0437FFF0FDCDFEFEFD63700F" box="[549,680,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.7mm</quantity>
. Scape pale brown to dark brown. Hind tibia and tarsus yellowishbrown to dark brown. Otherwise as in 
<typeStatus id="5482885A0437FFF0FDAEFEDAFD677053" box="[582,684,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8636F80437FFF0FF2FFEB6FE697077" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,1041]" box="[199,418,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FF2FFEB6FED57077" bold="true" box="[199,286,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32365730437FFF0FF2FFE92FA427397" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8636F80437FFF0FF2FFE92FA427397" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FF2FFE92FEFF709B" bold="true" box="[199,308,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">Remarks</emphasis>
. The sharp carina along anterior margin of the pronotal collar is a distinctive feature for this species. Two other species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FE9DFE6EFE3170BF" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[373,506,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicoxa">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FE9DFE6EFE3170BF" box="[373,506,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. albicoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FDDDFE6EFD6470BE" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[565,687,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FDDDFE6EFD6470BE" box="[565,687,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. cristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from females (males unknown) also have this feature. Specimens of both these species are predominantly yellowish-brown, while specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FB44FE4AFAF870C3" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[1196,1331,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinifer">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FB44FE4AFAF870C3" box="[1196,1331,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. carinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are dark brown to black. While the colour of head and mesosoma might differ between the sexes of the same species (see 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FA69FE26FF10730B" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FA69FE26FF10730B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and are thus unreliable characters when associating conspecific females and males, the dark areas in the fore wing are similar in both sexes. 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FE15FDDEFC90732F" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[509,859,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicoxa">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FE15FDDEFC90732F" box="[509,859,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">Diglyphomorphomyia albicoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FC7CFDDEFBC5732E" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[916,1038,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FC7CFDDEFBC5732E" box="[916,1038,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. cristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both have two distinct dark brown areas in the fore wing, one below marginal vein and one below stigmal vein (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0437FFF0FC1DFDBAFBF77373" box="[1013,1084,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-110@7.[151,1435,345,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 1–2. D. albiclava; 1 body in lateral view, paratype; 2 body in dorsal view, holotype; 3–4. D. albicoxa; 3 body in lateral view, paratype; 4 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592890/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0437FFF0FBA1FDBAFB927373" box="[1097,1113,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1784]" captionTargetId="figure-32@8.[151,1435,181,1784]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 5–6. D. costulata; 5 body in lateral view, holotype; 6 body in dorsal view, holotype; 7–8. D. cristata; 7 body in lateral view, paratype; 8 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592894/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">7</figureCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FB5BFDBAFAFC7373" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[1203,1335,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinifer">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FB5BFDBAFAFC7373" box="[1203,1335,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. carinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only part below stigmal vein dark (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D0437FFF0FE0FFD96FDF17397" box="[487,570,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-104@14.[151,1435,345,1797]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 17–18. D. carinifer; 17 body in lateral view, holotype; 18 body in dorsal view, paratype; 19–20. D. pedunculata; 19 body in dorsal view, paratype; 20 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Thus 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FD65FD96FCDA7397" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[653,785,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinifer">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FD65FD96FCDA7397" box="[653,785,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. carinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not conspecific with either 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FB8BFD96FB2E7397" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[1123,1253,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicoxa">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FB8BFD96FB2E7397" box="[1123,1253,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. albicoxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D7B0437FFF0FAE3FD96FA487396" authorityName="Hansson" authorityYear="2022" box="[1291,1411,619,644]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Diglyphomorphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA0437FFF0FAE3FD96FA487396" box="[1291,1411,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="326">D. cristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32365730437FFF0FF2FFD73FDAF73BB" box="[199,612,654,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="326" type="distribution">
